# {{COMPANY_NAME}} Orchestrator

Macro architectural truth for **{{COMPANY_NAME}}**'s stack — registered
sub-repos, contracts, conventions, decisions, migrations, roadmap.

This is a [claude-orchestrator](https://github.com/ChazzCoin/claude-orchestrator)
instance. It does not dispatch work to sub-kits and does not own a task
list. It holds truth, makes drift visible, and gives one reasoning
surface across software, infra, and product.

## Start a session

Open Claude Code in this directory. From there:

**Orient:**
- `/brief` — synthesized daily orientation (what changed, what's open, what's stuck)
- `/status` — current macro picture
- `/onboard` — full walkthrough for a new collaborator (or future-you)

**Populate / refresh state:**
- `/audit` — interview-driven macro audit (stack, contracts, conventions, constraints)
- `/register` — add a sub-repo to `state/manifest.md`

**File artifacts:**
- `/decision` — ADR
- `/feature` — cross-cutting feature plan
- `/migration` — open, update, list, close a cross-repo migration
- `/risk` — file or update a risk
- `/incident` — log a cross-stack incident + postmortem

**Recurring cadence:**
- `/review weekly` — Friday EOD or Monday AM (~15 min)
- `/review monthly` — first week of next month (~45 min)
- `/review quarterly` — first week of next quarter (~half-day, mandatory risk-surfacing pass)

**Drift / kit:**
- `/sync-check` — drift between sub-repos and orchestrator's contracts
- `/sync` — pull kit updates from upstream

Run `/skills` for the full live index.

## Sub-kit integration

Each sub-repo's `CLAUDE.md` should add a pointer back to this
orchestrator:

> **Macro architecture and contracts:** see `~/path/to/{{COMPANY_NAME}}-orchestrator/`.
> Read `stack/inventory.md`, `contracts/`, and any `features/<x>.md`
> matching current work before making cross-platform decisions.

The orchestrator can write migration notices into each sub-repo's
`.claude/active-migrations.md` so a sub-kit notices an open migration on
session start. That is the only orchestrator → sub-repo write path.

## Operating discipline

The CTO-level operating model — read order, artifact map, audit log
discipline, migration / risk / incident / review lifecycles — lives
in [`.claude/orchestrator-rules.md`](.claude/orchestrator-rules.md).
That file is kit-managed and synced via `/sync`.

This instance's CLAUDE.md holds company-specific behaviors and
identity; orchestrator-rules.md holds the generic discipline that
applies to every orchestrator instance.

## Where things live

- **Anchors:** `tech-vision.md`, `tech-principles.md`,
  `platform-constraints.md`
- **Active state:** `roadmap.md`, `open-questions.md`, `AUDIT.md`,
  `state/manifest.md`
- **Macro state:** `stack/`, `contracts/`, `conventions/`
- **Registries:** `vendors.md`, `ownership.md`, `slos.md`,
  `cost-tracking.md`, `security-posture.md`, `compliance.md`
- **Artifacts:** `decisions/`, `features/`,
  `migrations/{active,closed}/`, `risks/{open,mitigated}/`,
  `incidents/`, `reviews/{weekly,monthly,quarterly}/`

## Updates

Bootstrapped from the
[claude-orchestrator](https://github.com/ChazzCoin/claude-orchestrator)
kit. Run `/sync` to pull kit updates (skills, generic templates,
orchestrator-rules.md). Bootstrap content (CLAUDE.md, this README,
roadmap, anchors, registries, AUDIT, stack/, contracts/, conventions/,
state/manifest.md) belongs to this instance and is never touched by
`/sync`.
